.SH NAME
bls-btrfs-snapshots-completion-fish - Generate the autocompletion script for fish


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBbls-btrfs-snapshots completion fish [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Generate the autocompletion script for the fish shell.

.PP
To load completions in your current shell session:

.EX
bls-btrfs-snapshots completion fish | source
.EE

.PP
To load completions for every new session, execute once:

.EX
bls-btrfs-snapshots completion fish > ~/.config/fish/completions/bls-btrfs-snapshots.fish
.EE

.PP
You will need to start a new shell for this setup to take effect.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for fish

.PP
\fB--no-descriptions\fP[=false]
	disable completion descriptions


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB-c\fP, \fB--config\fP=""
	Path to config file (default: /etc/bls-btrfs-snapshots.yaml)

.PP
\fB--log-level\fP=""
	Log verbosity: trace, debug, info, warn, error


